<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="1935" pageId="2" pageNumber="1934" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[160,1156,1633,1728]" box="[160,280,1633,1659]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1934">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,280,1633,1659]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1934">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[160,1156,1633,1728]" lastBlockId="3.[160,1156,1495,1728]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="1935" pageId="2" pageNumber="1934">
Size 
<quantity box="[220,356,1669,1694]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.5" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="1934" unit="mm" value="90.0" valueMax="105.0" valueMin="75.0">75–105 µm</quantity>
× 
<quantity box="[402,523,1669,1694]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="1934" unit="mm" value="22.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="20.0">20–25 µm</quantity>
<emphasis box="[538,619,1669,1694]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1934">in vivo</emphasis>
. Body outline lanceolate with anterior end narrowly rounded and posterior end tapered, flexible but not contractile. Two macronuclear nodules, 2–4 micronuclei. Cortical granules lacking. Invariably 3 frontal cirri; 3–5 buccal cirri; frontoventral row III (excluding right frontal cirrus) composed of 4–6 cirri; frontoventral row IV extends beyond mid-body, composed of 12–23 cirri; frontoventral row V rather short, composed of 4–8 cirri. One left and one right marginal row, composed of 12–22 and 17–27 cirri, respectively. Three dorsal kineties arranged in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sterki" authorityYear="1878" box="[304,454,1669,1694]" class="Hypotrichea" family="Oxytrichidae" genus="Gonostomum" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Oxytrichida" pageId="3" pageNumber="1935" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[304,454,1669,1694]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1935">Gonostomum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-pattern and 3 caudal cirri. Adoral zone occupies about 33– 50% of body length, and is composed of 24–34 membranelles. Saline soil habitat.
</paragraph>
